# Theme Modes

- Any visual change must be checked for both dark and light mode, not just the currently active theme.
- When updating colors, backgrounds, borders, shadows, code blocks, cards, or text contrast, make sure the result feels intentional in both themes.
- Prefer theme-aware styles using existing CSS variables or explicit `html.light` overrides when the two themes need different tuning.
- Avoid shipping a styling change after validating only one mode.
- If a change looks right in dark mode but too heavy or low-contrast in light mode, add a light-mode-specific adjustment instead of compromising both.
